        <updateDate>2021-09-24T10:34:51Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>America Grows Act of 2021</strong></p> <p>This bill permanently funds several agencies that perform agriculture research. </p> <p>The bill provides specified funding for the following agencies within the Department of Agriculture:</p> <ul> <li>the Agricultural Research Service,</li> <li>the Economic Research Service,</li> <li>the National Agricultural Statistics Service, and</li> <li>the National Institute of Food and Agriculture.</li> </ul> <p>The bill exempts the funding from sequestration, which is a process of automatic, usually across-the-board spending reductions under which budgetary resources are permanently cancelled to enforce specific budget policy goals. </p> <p>It also exempts the budgetary effects of the funding from the Statutory Pay-As-You-Go Act of 2010 (PAYGO) and the Senate PAYGO rule. </p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
